    "message_1": "A math student is interested in studying the relationship between the number of hours spent studying and the grade they receive on a test. They collect data from 10 students in their class and compute the correlation coefficient to determine the strength and direction of the relationship. The data is as follows:\n\n| Hours spent studying | Test grade |\n|----------------------|------------|\n| 2                     | 70         |\n| 3                     | 85         |\n| 1                     | 60         |\n| 4                     | 90         |\n| 2                     | 72         |\n| 5                     | 95         |\n| 3                     | 80         |\n| 6                     | 98         |\n| 4                     | 85         |\n| 2                     | 68         |\n\nFind the correlation coefficient between the number of hours spent studying and the test grade. State the strength and direction of the relationship.",
    "message_2": "To find the correlation coefficient (r), we will use the following formula:\n\nr = Σ[(x - x̄)(y - ȳ)] / √[Σ(x - x̄)² * Σ(y - ȳ)²]\n\nFirst, we need to find the mean of the hours spent studying (x̄) and the mean of the test grades (ȳ).\n\nx̄ = (2 + 3 + 1 + 4 + 2 + 5 + 3 + 6 + 4 + 2) / 10 = 32 / 10 = 3.2\nȳ = (70 + 85 + 60 + 90 + 72 + 95 + 80 + 98 + 85 + 68) / 10 = 803 / 10 = 80.3\n\nNext, we will create a table to calculate the values needed for the formula:\n\n| Hours (x) | Test grade (y) | x - x̄ | y - ȳ | (x - x̄)(y - ȳ) | (x - x̄)² | (y - ȳ)² |\n|-----------|----------------|-------|-------|---------------|-------|-------|\n| 2         | 70             | -1.2  | -10.3 | 12.36          | 1.44  | 106.09|\n| 3         | 85             | -0.2  | 4.7   | -0.94          | 0.04  | 22.09 |\n| 1         | 60             | -2.2  | -20.3 | 44.66          | 4.84  | 412.09|\n| 4         | 90             | 0.8   | 9.7   | 7.76           | 0.64  | 94.09 |\n| 2         | 72             | -1.2  | -8.3  | 9.96           | 1.44  | 68.89 |\n| 5         | 95             | 1.8   | 14.7  | 26.46          | 3.24  | 216.09|\n| 3         | 80             | -0.2  | -0.3  | 0.06           | 0.04  | 0.09  |\n| 6         | 98             | 2.8   | 17.7  | 49.56          | 7.84  | 313.29|\n| 4         | 85             | 0.8   | 4.7   | 3.76           | 0.64  | 22.09 |\n| 2         | 68             | -1.2  | -12.3 | 14.76          | 1.44  | 151.29|\n\nNow, we can calculate the sums needed for the formula:\n\nΣ(x - x̄)(y - ȳ) = 12.36 - 0.94 + 44.66 + 7.76 + 9.96 + 26.46 + 0.06 + 49.56 + 3.76 + 14.76 = 168.4\nΣ(x - x̄)² = 1.44 + 0.04 + 4.84 + 0.64 + 1.44 + 3.24 + 0.04 + 7.84 + 0.64 + 1.44 = 21.6\nΣ(y - ȳ)² = 106.09 + 22.09 + 412.09 + 94.09 + 68.89 + 216.09 + 0.09 + 313.29 + 22.09 + 151.29 = 1405.2\n\nFinally, we can plug these values into the formula:\n\nr = 168.4 / √(21.6 * 1405.2) ≈ 168.4 / √(30323.52) ≈ 168.4 / 174.137 ≈ 0.967\n\nThe correlation coefficient (r) is approximately 0.967. This indicates a strong positive relationship between the number of hours spent studying and the test grade."
